description:
This is a 6 minute workout called 'Head of the Kevin Bow View' from the channel Unknown.
The workout falls under Cardio/Indoor rowing.
It's suitable for Beginner and Intermediate fitness levels.
You'll need Rower for this workout.
The workout has a The Nature Flow and The Mindful Walk vibe.
The The Nature Flow vibe means Breath-centered, full-body, outdoor rhythm. This is especially good for When you want fresh air, nature, and full-body movement. The The Mindful Walk vibe means Meditative, story-driven, immersive. This is especially good for When you need fresh air, a change of pace, and mental clarity..
The technique difficulty is Beginner and Intermediate.
The effort required is Moderate.

Original workout description: Race down the Charles River during the Head of the Kevin Regatta, an annual race in Boston. ...
